We further examined the full-cell CO2 electrolysis performance in a compact, commercialization-relevant MEA system (electrode geometric area = 4 cm2). Cu(OH)BTA catalysts were used as the cathode while iridium oxide supported on titanium mesh (IrO2/Ti) were used as the anode, and they were separated by an anion exchange membrane (Supplementary Figs. 17 and 18). The overall reaction is12CO2+2H2O→C2H4+3O2;Eo=1.15V\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
